<br>
(600 second burn at 80Gw per engine . Its only a rough guess to get a ballpark feel)<br>
<br>
As for the Pacific question. You are, of course, correct that bad consequences can occur if it all goes horribly wrong. ISTM that a failure to achieve orbit may be the worse of the two since the rocket would then become, essentially, a ballistic missile with an unpredictable range/heading. The best abort position might well be to flush the reactors out at altitude rather than to let them crash containing their FP's Ill have to think more about this one<br>
<br>
